  <body>
    <p><italic>Chin RFM, Neville BGR, Peckham C, Wade A, Bedford H, Scott RC. Treatment of community-onset, childhood convulsive status epilepticus: a prospective, population-based study</italic>. Lancet Neurol <italic>2008; <bold>7:</bold> 696–703.</italic> In figure 1, the breakdown of the dose regimens given as first-line AED that led to seizure termination is incorrect. The text should read: “There were 121 seizure terminations after first-line AEDs: 42 after treatment with single dose intravenous lorazepam; 23 after treatment with two or more doses of lorazepam; 9 after a single dose of rectal diazepam; 47 after two or more doses of rectal diazepam, or rectal diazepam followed by one or more doses of intravenous lorazepam”. The title of table 3 is incorrect. The correct title is: “Logistic regression analyses of factors associated with seizure terminations after second-line AED”.</p>
